                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.933/94: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-08-06T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 6, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 6—6:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>675. Your telegram No. 254, August 1, 11 a.m.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>It has on consultation been arranged that the American, British, Dutch and
                        French replies will be dated August 10th and delivered to Nationalist
                        Foreign Office, August 12th. Brazilian and Norwegian Legations are being so
                        informed with a view to their taking similar action.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>It has all along been understood that the replies would not be identical
                        although of similar tenor.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
